{
  "name": "milestone-m1b-from-docs-state-20260416-1226",
  "idea": "Milestone M1b from docs/state_management_refactor_plan.md \u2014 Selection store.\n\nGoal: collapse five separate selection-state surfaces (four React contexts + an inline state machine in `useTimelineState`) into one Zustand store at `src/shared/state/selectionStore.ts` with three slices (`gallery`, `timeline`, `shot`). Cross-context effect-chain syncs (the \"X changed \u2192 fire effect \u2192 write to Y context \u2192 fire effect again\") become explicit store actions.\n\nThis milestone DEPENDS on M1's `createEntityStore` factory pattern (or its slicing equivalent) being available. M1a does NOT need to be merged before M1b \u2014 they touch different state domains.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n1. **`src/shared/state/selectionStore.ts`** \u2014 single Zustand store with three slices:\n   - `gallery`: state currently in `src/shared/contexts/GallerySelectionContext.tsx`\n   - `timeline`: selection state currently inline in `src/tools/video-editor/hooks/useTimelineState.ts`\n   - `shot`: state currently spread across `LastAffectedShotContext.tsx`, `CurrentShotContext.tsx`, `ShotAdditionSelectionContext.tsx`\n\n   Each slice is a self-contained sub-store (use Zustand's slice pattern). Selectors return stable references via `shallow` equality where they return objects/arrays.\n\n2. **Delete the four contexts** after migration:\n   - `src/shared/contexts/GallerySelectionContext.tsx`\n   - `src/shared/contexts/LastAffectedShotContext.tsx`\n   - `src/shared/contexts/CurrentShotContext.tsx`\n   - `src/shared/contexts/ShotAdditionSelectionContext.tsx`\n\n   (Verify exact paths + filenames at milestone start. If a context has been renamed, update the deletion list.)\n\n3. **Migrate the inline timeline selection state** out of `useTimelineState.ts` into the `timeline` slice. Leave the rest of `useTimelineState` alone (that's M1c's job).\n\n4. **Convert effect-chain syncs to actions**. Today, several places do \"context A changes \u2192 useEffect fires \u2192 write to context B \u2192 its consumers' effects fire \u2192 ...\" Each such chain becomes a single action on the store that updates all relevant slices atomically.\n   - Discover the chains by running the app and observing actual behavior, not by trying to read effect graphs cold. The meta plan explicitly says \"discover the behaviors by using the app \u2014 don't write a matrix up front.\"\n   - Document each converted chain in the PR with a before/after sketch.\n\n5. **Migrate every consumer**. At milestone start, run:\n   ```\n   rg 'GallerySelectionContext|LastAffectedShotContext|CurrentShotContext|ShotAdditionSelectionContext' src/ --type ts -l\n   ```\n   Paste the list into the PR. Migrate each file to use the store via selectors.\n\n## Gate criteria \u2014 MUST (hard blockers)\n\n- **Every selection-dependent UX behavior preserved** across gallery \u2194 timeline \u2194 shot. Examples to manually verify (not exhaustive \u2014 discover others by use):\n  - Selecting a clip in the timeline highlights the corresponding asset in the gallery.\n  - Selecting a shot in the shots pane updates \"current shot\" everywhere.\n  - \"Last affected shot\" updates correctly after edits/generations.\n  - Shot-addition flow's selection state survives the addition.\n- **Per-domain renders confined to that domain** \u2014 verify with the M0 telemetry overlay that selecting a gallery item does not cause timeline-only components to re-render, and vice versa. Capture before/after counts in the PR.\n- **`npx tsc --noEmit` clean**.\n- **Test suite matches M0 baseline pass count** \u2014 any net regression blocks.\n\n## Decision point at gate\n\nPer the meta plan:\n- **If regressions cluster in one area** (e.g., shot selection breaks repeatedly across iterations) \u2192 re-scope the next milestone (M1c) to fix the root cause first. Document the cluster in the PR and surface it as a flag.\n- **Otherwise** \u2192 continue to M1c.\n\n## Repo conventions (from reigh-app/CLAUDE.md)\n\n- Prefer editing existing files; new files are limited to `selectionStore.ts` itself.\n- No hardcoded colors. No `any`. TypeScript strict.\n- Don't modify edge functions, supabase migrations, or worker-orchestrator code.\n- Don't touch settings persistence (M1a) or timeline non-selection state (M1c).\n- Don't add Zustand devtools, persist middleware, or other non-essential cross-cutting patterns.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Settings persistence (M1a \u2014 separate domain).\n- Timeline non-selection state \u2014 clip data, playback, chrome (M1c).\n- Overlay stack (M2 \u2014 conditional).\n- Realtime/task store (M3).\n- Panes store (M4).\n- React Query behavior changes.\n\n## Branch\n\n`megaplan/m1b-selection-store` off `main`. Pull latest `main` first.\n\n## Base commit note\n\nIf M1, M1a, or both have unmerged branches on GitHub when this starts, that's OK \u2014 M1b only depends on the factory pattern existing in `main`. Halt and surface if `src/shared/state/createEntityStore.ts` is absent.",
